  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-12"><div class="rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 sm:p-8 md:p-10 card-shadow"><div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8"><div class="space-y-5"><div><label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Pay Type</label><select id="pay-type" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-slate-300 p-4"><option value="salary">Annual Salary</option><option value="hourly">Hourly</option></select></div><div><label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Annual Salary ($)</label><input id="annual-salary" type="number" value="65000" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-slate-300 p-4"></div><div id="hourly-wrap" class="hidden grid grid-cols-2 gap-4"><div><label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Hourly Rate ($)</label><input id="hourly-rate" type="number" value="32" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-slate-300 p-4"></div><div><label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Hours/Week</label><input id="hours-week" type="number" value="40" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-slate-300 p-4"></div></div><div><label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Pay Period</label><select id="pay-period" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-slate-300 p-4"><option value="monthly">Monthly</option><option value="biweekly">Bi-Weekly</option><option value="weekly">Weekly</option></select></div></div><div class="space-y-5"><div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4"><div><label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Federal Tax (%)</label><input id="fed-tax" type="number" value="22" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-slate-300 p-4"></div><div><label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">State Tax (%)</label><input id="state-tax" type="number" value="5" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-slate-300 p-4"></div></div><div><label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">401k Contribution (%)</label><input id="retirement" type="number" value="4" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-slate-300 p-4"></div><div><label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Health Insurance ($ per period)</label><input id="health" type="number" value="80" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-slate-300 p-4"></div><button onclick="calculate()" class="w-full rounded-2xl bg-emerald-600 py-4 font-semibold text-white hover:bg-emerald-700">Calculate Take-Home Pay</button></div></div><div id="result" class="mt-8"></div><div id="decision-state" class="mt-6" hidden><div class="rounded-2xl border p-6" data-decision-state><p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold" data-state-eyebrow></p><h3 class="mt-2 text-xl font-bold" data-state-label></h3><p class="mt-3 text-slate-700" data-state-body></p><div class="mt-4 rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4"><p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Recommended next step</p><p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-700" data-next-step-text></p><a class="inline-block mt-2 text-emerald-700 font-medium" data-next-step-link>Open the next calculator →</a></div><p class="mt-4 text-xs text-slate-500">This is an educational estimate. Real outcomes depend on your full situation. Talk to a qualified professional before making major decisions.</p></div></div></div></section>
bodyHtml: |
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-12"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Why this tool matters in 2026</h2><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">Estimate monthly, biweekly, or weekly net pay after federal tax, state tax, Social Security, Medicare, 401k, and insurance deductions. This free take-home pay calculator is useful for employees comparing job offers, freelancers reviewing contract rates, and anyone building a more realistic monthly budget for 2026. Good planning works best when you connect this page with the rest of your workflow on Finance Tools Hub.</p></div></section>

  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-4"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">What this calculator does</h2><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">This page estimates net take-home pay after common payroll deductions. It is designed to show the difference between gross compensation and the amount that may actually arrive in your paycheck after taxes, retirement savings, and health insurance are deducted.</p><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">That makes it valuable when evaluating job offers, pay raises, hourly versus salary work, or the monthly affordability of housing, debt payments, and other fixed costs.</p></div></section>
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-4"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">How the estimate works</h2><div class="mt-6 space-y-4"><div class="rounded-2xl bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-100 p-5"><p class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Gross Pay − Federal Tax − State Tax − Social Security − Medicare − 401(k) − Health Insurance = Estimated Net Pay</p></div></div><p class="mt-6 text-slate-600">This is a planning formula. Real paychecks can differ based on pre-tax benefits, local taxes, withholding elections, filing status, and employer-specific deductions.</p></div></section>
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-4"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Common scenarios</h2><div class="mt-5 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4"><div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5"><h3 class="font-semibold">The job offer comparison</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">Which salary actually gives me more usable cash after taxes and benefits instead of just a higher gross number?</p></div><div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5"><h3 class="font-semibold">The hourly worker</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">How much will I likely take home if I work 40 hours a week at a new hourly rate?</p></div><div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5"><h3 class="font-semibold">The household planner</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">Can my expected paycheck realistically support rent, debt payments, savings, and insurance each month?</p></div></div></div></section>
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-4"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Sources and methodology</h2><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">This calculator is an educational take-home pay estimate. Actual withholding can vary significantly.</p><ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 text-slate-600 space-y-2"><li>Payroll deductions vary by employer, state, benefit setup, and withholding elections.</li><li>Social Security and Medicare estimates here are simplified for planning.</li><li>Use the <a class="text-emerald-700 font-medium" href="/methodology.html">Methodology page</a> to review how Finance Tools Hub approaches assumptions and transparency.</li></ul><div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3"><a href="/methodology.html" class="px-4 py-3 rounded-full bg-slate-900 text-white font-medium">Read methodology</a><a href="/about.html" class="px-4 py-3 rounded-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-800 font-medium">About the site</a><a href="/author-renato-bryant.html" class="px-4 py-3 rounded-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-800 font-medium">Author profile</a></div></div></section>

calcScript: |
  // Default inputs (annual=$65000, monthly periods, fed=22%, state=5%, 401k=4%, health=$80) land on: lower-take-home (amber). netRatio ≈ 0.599 — sits ~0.001 below the 0.60 typical-cash-flow threshold.
  function calculate(){
   let annual = parseFloat(document.getElementById('annual-salary').value)||0;
   const isHourly = document.getElementById('pay-type').value==='hourly';
   if(isHourly){ annual=(parseFloat(document.getElementById('hourly-rate').value)||0)*(parseFloat(document.getElementById('hours-week').value)||0)*52; }
   const period = document.getElementById('pay-period').value; const periods=period==='monthly'?12:period==='biweekly'?26:52;
   const fed=(parseFloat(document.getElementById('fed-tax').value)||0)/100, state=(parseFloat(document.getElementById('state-tax').value)||0)/100, ret=(parseFloat(document.getElementById('retirement').value)||0)/100, health=(parseFloat(document.getElementById('health').value)||0);
   const gross=annual/periods, taxes=gross*(fed+state+0.062+0.0145), retDed=gross*ret, total=taxes+retDed+health, net=gross-total;
   const result={'Annual Income':'$'+annual.toFixed(2),'Gross Per Period':'$'+gross.toFixed(2),'Total Deductions':'$'+total.toFixed(2),'Net Take-Home Pay':'$'+net.toFixed(2)};
   document.getElementById('result').innerHTML=`<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4"><div class="result-card"><p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Gross per period</p><p class="text-3xl font-bold">$${gross.toFixed(2)}</p></div><div class="result-card"><p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Deductions</p><p class="text-3xl font-bold text-red-600">-$${total.toFixed(2)}</p></div><div class="result-card bg-emerald-50"><p class="text-sm text-emerald-700">Net Pay</p><p class="text-4xl font-bold text-emerald-700">$${net.toFixed(2)}</p></div></div><div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-6"><button class="px-5 py-3 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900 text-white" onclick='downloadResultPDF("Take-Home Pay Calculator", ${JSON.stringify(result)})'>Download PDF</button><button class="px-5 py-3 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-600 text-white" onclick='emailResult("Take-Home Pay Calculator", ${JSON.stringify(result)})'>Send by Email</button><button class="px-4 py-3 rounded-2xl border" onclick='shareUrl("X","Take-Home Pay Calculator")'>X</button><button class="px-4 py-3 rounded-2xl border" onclick='shareUrl("Facebook","Take-Home Pay Calculator")'>Facebook</button><button class="px-4 py-3 rounded-2xl border" onclick='shareUrl("LinkedIn","Take-Home Pay Calculator")'>LinkedIn</button><button class="px-4 py-3 rounded-2xl border" onclick='shareUrl("WhatsApp","Take-Home Pay Calculator")'>WhatsApp</button></div>`;
   const netRatio = gross > 0 ? net / gross : 0;
   if (netRatio >= 0.70) setDecisionState('strong-cash-flow', 'emerald', 'Strong cash flow', "Your take-home is on the higher end of typical for your inputs. You're keeping a solid share of gross pay after taxes and benefits.", "Consider whether your retirement contribution rate is high enough — try the Retirement Savings Calculator.", '/retirement-savings-calculator.html');
   else if (netRatio >= 0.60) setDecisionState('typical-cash-flow', 'slate', 'Typical cash flow', "Your take-home is roughly typical for the inputs you provided. Most US W-2 workers fall in this band.", "If you have side income, model self-employment tax separately with the Gig Tax Optimizer.", '/gig-tax-optimizer.html');
   else setDecisionState('lower-take-home', 'amber', 'Lower take-home', "Your take-home is on the lower end relative to gross pay. High deductions, high tax rate, or expensive benefits could be the cause.", "Use the Tax Bracket Calculator to see how much of this is federal tax versus other deductions.", '/tax-bracket-calculator.html');
   }
  document.getElementById('pay-type').addEventListener('change', ()=>{ const h=document.getElementById('hourly-wrap'); h.classList.toggle('hidden', document.getElementById('pay-type').value!=='hourly'); });
  function setDecisionState(stateKey, color, label, body, nextText, nextHref) {
    const wrap = document.getElementById('decision-state');
    if (!wrap) return;
    const card = wrap.querySelector('[data-decision-state]');
    card.className = 'rounded-2xl border p-6';
    const colorMap = { emerald: 'bg-emerald-50 border-emerald-200', slate: 'bg-slate-50 border-slate-200', amber: 'bg-amber-50 border-amber-200', red: 'bg-red-50 border-red-200' };
    card.classList.add(...colorMap[color].split(' '));
    card.dataset.state = stateKey;
    card.querySelector('[data-state-eyebrow]').textContent = 'Decision state';
    card.querySelector('[data-state-label]').textContent = label;
    card.querySelector('[data-state-body]').textContent = body;
    card.querySelector('[data-next-step-text]').textContent = nextText;
    const link = card.querySelector('[data-next-step-link]');
    link.href = nextHref;
    wrap.hidden = false;
  }
